ğŸ§  What is Linux?

Linux is an open-source operating system kernel created by Linus Torvalds (1991).
It forms the foundation of many server operating systems like RHEL, Ubuntu, and CentOS.

Feature	Description
Open Source	Free to modify and distribute
Multiuser	Multiple users can log in simultaneously
Multitasking	Multiple tasks at the same time
Secure	Permissions, SELinux
Scalable	Used from laptops to servers
ğŸŸ¥ What is RHEL?

RHEL (Red Hat Enterprise Linux) is a commercial Linux distribution by Red Hat Inc.

Used in enterprise and cloud environments

Supports automation, containers, virtualization

Comes with subscription-based updates & support

ğŸ–¥ï¸ Accessing RHEL
Access Type	Example
Local Access	Login to console or GUI
Remote Access	ssh cloud-user@<server-ip>
ğŸ§© Shell & Terminal Basics

Linux uses a command-line interface (CLI) known as the shell.

Common shells:

bash (default)

sh

zsh

Check current shell:

echo $SHELL

ğŸ“‚ File System Hierarchy
Directory	Purpose
/	Root of file system
/home	User directories
/etc	Configuration files
/var	Logs, variable files
/usr	Installed programs
/tmp	Temporary files
/dev	Device files
/boot	Kernel & bootloader files
ğŸ”¹ Common Commands
whoami          # Show current user
hostname        # System name
pwd             # Present directory
ls -l           # List files
cd /etc         # Change directory
mkdir test      # Create directory
rm -r test      # Remove directory
date            # System date
cal             # Calendar
clear           # Clear screen

ğŸ§  Help Commands
man ls          # Show manual page
ls --help       # Quick syntax help
which cp        # Locate command path
man -k copy     # Search manual

