ğŸŸ¦ Module 2: User, Group & Permission Management
ğŸ¯ Objectives

Create and manage users/groups

Apply Linux file permissions

Manage access control (ACL)

ğŸ‘¤ User Management
useradd john
passwd john
userdel -r john


View users:

cat /etc/passwd

ğŸ‘¥ Group Management
groupadd devops
usermod -aG devops john
groups john


View groups:

cat /etc/group

ğŸ” Permissions
Symbol	Meaning	Value
r	Read	4
w	Write	2
x	Execute	1

Example:

chmod 755 script.sh
chown john:devops file.txt


ACLs:

setfacl -m u:bob:rw file.txt
getfacl file.txt

ğŸŸ¨ Module 3: File System & Storage Management
ğŸ¯ Objectives

Partition, format, and mount disks

Configure LVM

Persistent mounting

Disk Commands

lsblk
fdisk -l
blkid


Partition Creation

fdisk /dev/xvdb
mkfs.xfs /dev/xvdb1
mkdir /data
mount /dev/xvdb1 /data


Persistent Mount
Edit /etc/fstab:

/dev/xvdb1 /data xfs defaults 0 0


LVM Setup

pvcreate /dev/xvdc
vgcreate vgdata /dev/xvdc
lvcreate -L 5G -n lvbackup vgdata
mkfs.xfs /dev/vgdata/lvbackup
mount /dev/vgdata/lvbackup /backup

ğŸŸ© Module 4: Process and Service Management
ğŸ¯ Objectives

Manage running processes

Control services via systemd

Process Commands

